Here's a complete guide covering all three requirements:

## 1. Detect the Current System Theme

```csharp
AppTheme current = Application.Current!.RequestedTheme;
// Returns AppTheme.Light, AppTheme.Dark, or AppTheme.Unspecified
```

## 2. Subscribe to Real-Time Theme Changes

```csharp
// In your App constructor or page initialization:
Application.Current!.RequestedThemeChanged += (s, e) =>
{
    AppTheme newTheme = e.RequestedTheme;
    Debug.WriteLine($"Theme changed to: {newTheme}");

    // Optionally swap full ResourceDictionaries:
    ApplyTheme(newTheme == AppTheme.Dark
        ? new DarkTheme()
        : new LightTheme());
};
```

## 3. Force a Specific Theme (User Override)

```csharp
// Force dark mode regardless of OS
Application.Current!.UserAppTheme = AppTheme.Dark;

// Force light mode
Application.Current!.UserAppTheme = AppTheme.Light;

// Reset to follow system
Application.Current!.UserAppTheme = AppTheme.Unspecified;
```

Persist the choice across launches:

```csharp
// Save
Preferences.Set("AppTheme", "Dark");

// Restore on startup (App constructor)
var saved = Preferences.Get("AppTheme", "System");
Application.Current!.UserAppTheme = saved switch
{
    "Light" => AppTheme.Light,
    "Dark"  => AppTheme.Dark,
    _       => AppTheme.Unspecified
};
```

## ⚠️ Critical Android Pitfall

Your `MainActivity` **must** include `ConfigChanges.UiMode` or theme events won't fire (the activity restarts instead):

```csharp
[Activity(Theme = "@style/Maui.SplashTheme",
          MainLauncher = true,
          ConfigurationChanges = ConfigChanges.ScreenSize
                               | ConfigChanges.Orientation
                               | ConfigChanges.UiMode  // ← Required!
                               | ConfigChanges.ScreenLayout
                               | ConfigChanges.SmallestScreenSize
                               | ConfigChanges.Density)]
public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity { }
```

## XAML: Auto Light/Dark with No Code

For simple cases, `AppThemeBinding` in XAML responds automatically:

```xml
<Label Text="Hello"
       TextColor="{AppThemeBinding Light=Green, Dark=Red}"
       BackgroundColor="{AppThemeBinding Light=White, Dark=Black}" />
```

Use **`DynamicResource`** (not `StaticResource`) if you're swapping `ResourceDictionary` themes at runtime — `StaticResource` freezes at first load.
